1 packet beef mince
1 carrot
½ head cos lettuce
1 cucumber
1 packet garlic aioli
8 Mini Flour Tortillas
olive oil
1 onion
1.5 tbs soy sauce
¼ cup rice wine vinegar (or white wine vinegar)
1 packet Sichuan garlic paste

• Thinly slice red onion. In a small bowl, combine rice wine vinegar and a good pinch of sugar and salt.
• Scrunch 1/2 the onion in your hands, then add to pickling liquid with just enough water to cover onion. Stir to coat. Set aside until serving.
• Thinly slice cucumber into long sticks. Grate carrot. Shred cos lettuce (see ingredients).
• In a small bowl, combine soy sauce and Sichuan garlic paste.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Cook beef mince and remaining onion, breaking mince up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Remove from heat, then add soy-Sichuan mixture and cook, stirring, until heated through.

• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate for 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

• Drain pickled onion. Bring everything to the table to serve.
• Build your tacos by spreading some garlic aioli over a tortilla. Top with some cos lettuce, cucumber, carrot, Sichuan beef and pickled onion.